2026-03-28 11:43:12 - Agent_20260328113756 - INFO - [+] Agent signaled completion: Reviewed 9 CodeQL queries covering XSS vulnerabilities across Nacos config/naming modules. Key findings:

TRUE POSITIVES (8):
1. TrafficReviseFilter (line 102-104): Writes response without Content-Type header set - allows browser MIME sniffing
2-7. RaftController (lines 189, 229, 249, 278, 302, 344): User-controlled Accept-Charset header reflected directly into Content-Type response header via getAcceptEncoding() without CRLF validation - HTTP response header injection across 6 endpoints
8. ConfigServletInner (lines 101-102): User-derived MD5/config keys added to response headers without CRLF sanitization
9. UserController (line 213): JWT token placed in Authorization header without CRLF validation

FALSE POSITIVES (3):
1. WebUtils.response() (line 177): Content-Type explicitly set to application/json before writing - mitigates XSS
2. LongPollingService (line 524): Output is URL-encoded before writing to response - mitigates XSS  
3. ConfigServletInner (lines 230, 251, 289): Fixed strings or stored config content written - not reflected user input

The most significant vulnerability pattern is the CRLF injection via Accept-Charset header across all RaftController endpoints, which could allow attackers to inject arbitrary HTTP response headers.
